14 Appendix C: Schema Definitions

Appendix C provides the schema definitions for the implementation guide and message profiles. A map of the structure and design of the schemas is given in Section 10, Computable Document Definitions.

14.1 ImplementationGuide.xsd

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<!-- ========================================================================================================

HL7 Implementation Guide Schema

============================================================================================================= -->

<xs:schema xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:vc="http://www.w3.org/2007/XMLSchema-versioning" vc:minVersion="1.1">

<!-- INCLUDE DataElement Properties -->

<xs:include schemaLocation="./library/HL7v2DataElementAttributes.xsd"/>

<!-- INCLUDE Message Profile ID -->

<xs:include schemaLocation="./library/MessageProfileID.xsd"/>

<!-- INCLUDE Slicing -->

<xs:include schemaLocation="./library/Slicing.xsd"/>

<!--

=============================================================================================================

========================= Root Element Definition =======================================

============================================================================================================= -->

<xs:element name="ImplementationGuide" type="ImplementationGuideType">

<!-- Segment ID must be unique within Segments element-->

<xs:key name="SegmentKey">

<xs:selector xpath="./Segments/Segment"/>

<xs:field xpath="@ID"/>

</xs:key>

<!-- Message ID must be unique within Messages element-->

<xs:key name="MessageKey">

<xs:selector xpath="./Messages/Message"/>

<xs:field xpath="@ID"/>

</xs:key>

<!-- Segment in a message must reference an existing Segment -->

<xs:keyref name="MSegmentKeyRef" refer="SegmentKey">

<xs:selector xpath=".//Segment"/>

<xs:field xpath="@Ref"/>

</xs:keyref>

</xs:element>

<!--

=============================================================================================================

========================= Metadata Types Definitions =======================================

============================================================================================================= -->

<xs:complexType name="BaseMetaDataType">

<xs:sequence>

<xs:element name="Authors" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>List of authors that created the implementation guide/message profile.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

<xs:complexType>

<xs:sequence>

<xs:element name="Author" type="NonEmptyString" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded"/>

</xs:sequence>

</xs:complexType>

</xs:element>

</xs:sequence>

<xs:attribute name="Name" type="NonEmptyString" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The natural language name of the implementation guide/message profile.

Commonly used as the title of the implementation guide/message profile.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="Description" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>Provides a short summary and intended use of the implementation guide/message profile.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="Version" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The version of the implementation guide/message profile as decided by the author. There is no prescribed format.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="Organization" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The name/identification of the organization or owner of the implementation guide/message profile.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="CreateDate" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The date the implementation guide/message profile was created. YYYYMMDD</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="LastUpdateDate" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The date the implementation guide/message profile was last updated. YYYYMMDD</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="Status" type="StatusType" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The status of the implementation guide/message profile.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="PublishDate" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>If the status is “publish”, this is the date the implementation guide/message profile was published. Once published, the version is static.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

</xs:complexType>

<xs:complexType name="ImplementationGuideMetadataType">

<xs:complexContent>

<xs:extension base="BaseMetaDataType">

<xs:sequence>

<xs:element name="HL7Versions" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>List of HL7 profile versions included in the implementation guide. Generally, most implementation guides include message profiles of the same HL7 version.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

<xs:complexType>

<xs:sequence>

<xs:element name="Version" type="HL7VersionType" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded"/>

</xs:sequence>

</xs:complexType>

</xs:element>

</xs:sequence>

</xs:extension>

</xs:complexContent>

</xs:complexType>

<xs:complexType name="MessageProfileMetadataType">

<xs:complexContent>

<xs:extension base="BaseMetaDataType">

<xs:attribute name="HL7Version" type="HL7VersionType" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The HL7 core version of the message profile; i.e., the version of the HL7 v2 abstract message definition. Corresponds to MSH-12.1. Value is obtained from table HL70104.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="MessageCode" type="MessageCodeType" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The HL7 v2 Message Code (e.g., ADT). Corresponds to MSH-9.1. Value is obtained from table HL70076.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="TriggerEvent" type="TriggerEventType" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The HL7 v2 Trigger Event (e.g., A04). Corresponds to MSH-9.2. Value is obtained from table HL70003.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="MessageStructure" type="MessageStructureType" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The HL7 v2 Message Structure (e.g., ADT_A01). Corresponds to MSH-9.3. Value is obtained from table HL70354.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="Type" type="MessageTypeType" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The type (level) of message profiles.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="Role" type="RoleType" use="optional">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>The role (perspective) of the message profile.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

</xs:extension>

14.2 DatatypeLibrary.xsd

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<!-- ========================================================================================================

HL7 Datatype Library Schema

============================================================================================================= -->

<xs:schema xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">

<!-- INCLUDE DataElement Properties -->

<xs:include schemaLocation="./library/HL7v2DataElementAttributes.xsd"/>

<xs:element name="Datatypes">

<xs:complexType>

<xs:sequence>

<xs:element name="Datatype" type="DatatypeType" minOccurs="1" maxOccurs="unbounded"/>

</xs:sequence>

</xs:complexType>

<!-- Datatype ID must be unique within Datatypes element-->

<xs:key name="DatatypeKey">

<xs:selector xpath="./Datatype"/>

<xs:field xpath="@ID"/>

</xs:key>

<!-- Component must reference an existing Datatype -->

<xs:keyref name="ComponentDatatypeKeyRef" refer="DatatypeKey">

<xs:selector xpath="./Datatype/Component"/>

<xs:field xpath="@Datatype"/>

</xs:keyref>

</xs:element>

<xs:complexType name="DatatypeType">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>Provides descriptive information about the life-cycle of the HL7 v2x Static Definition, as well as authorship and control information.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

<xs:sequence>

<xs:element name="Annotation" type="AnnotationType" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded"/>

<xs:element name="Component" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="unbounded">

<xs:complexType>

<xs:complexContent>

<xs:extension base="DataElementType"/>

</xs:complexContent>

</xs:complexType>

</xs:element>

</xs:sequence>

<xs:attribute name="ID" type="DatatypeNameType" use="required"/>

<xs:attribute name="Name" type="NonEmptyString" use="required"/>

<xs:attribute name="Label" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional"/>

<xs:attribute name="Description" type="NonEmptyString" use="required"/>

<xs:attribute name="AdoptedVersion" type="HL7VersionType" use="optional"/>

</xs:complexType>

</xs:schema>

14.3 Constraints.xsd

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<xs:schema xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" elementFormDefault="qualified">

<xs:include schemaLocation="./library/Expressions.xsd"/>

<!-- =============================================================================================================

========================= MetaData Definition =======================================

============================================================================================================= -->

<xs:complexType name="Author">

<xs:attribute name="FirstName" type="NonEmptyString" use="required"/>

<xs:attribute name="LastName" type="NonEmptyString" use="required"/>

<xs:attribute name="Email" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional"/>

</xs:complexType>

<xs:complexType name="StandardType">

<xs:sequence>

<xs:sequence>

<xs:element name="Description" minOccurs="0" maxOccurs="1"/>

</xs:sequence>

</xs:sequence>

<xs:attribute name="ID" type="NonEmptyString" use="required"/>

<xs:attribute name="Version" type="NonEmptyString" use="required"/>

<xs:attribute name="Date" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional"/>

<xs:attribute name="URL" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional"/>

</xs:complexType>

<xs:complexType name="MetaDataType">

<xs:attribute name="Name" type="NonEmptyString" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>Name of this Constraints ex) Constraints for VXU-Z22/_Profile.xml</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="OrgName" type="NonEmptyString" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>Organization Name of this Constraints ex) NIST</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="Version" type="NonEmptyString" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>Version of this Constraints ex) 1.0.0</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="Date" type="NonEmptyString" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>Date of this Constraints ex) YYYYMMDD</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="SpecificationName" type="xs:string" use="optional">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>Provides a name that clearly and concisely defines the Constraints being described.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="Status" use="optional">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>Status of this Constraints, as assigned by the author. There is no prescribed status scheme at this time. Possible values might include: 'Draft', 'Active', 'Superceded', 'Withdrawn'</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

<xs:simpleType>

<xs:restriction base="xs:string">

<xs:enumeration value="Draft"/>

<xs:enumeration value="Active"/>

<xs:enumeration value="Superceded"/>

<xs:enumeration value="Withdrawn"/>

</xs:restriction>

</xs:simpleType>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="Topics" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>This provides a list of key-words that relate to the Constraints and that may be useful in valueset searches.</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

</xs:complexType>

<xs:complexType name="ReferenceType">

<xs:attribute name="Chapter" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional"/>

<xs:attribute name="Section" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional"/>

<xs:attribute name="Page" type="PositiveInteger" use="optional"/>

<xs:attribute name="URL" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional"/>

<xs:attribute name="Source" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional"/>

<xs:attribute name="GeneratedBy" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional"/>

<xs:attribute name="ReferencePath" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional"/>

<xs:attribute name="TestDataCategorization" type="NonEmptyString" use="optional"/>

<!-- The following have been added to provide more meta data to a constraint -->

</xs:complexType>

<xs:attribute name="Min" type="PositiveInteger" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>

This identifies the minimum number of repetitions of the element that are permitted in a message instance. This attribute should

only be specified if the minimum number of repetitions is greater than 1, as the minimum for other elements is always '0'.

</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:attribute name="Max" type="IntegerOrStar" use="required">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>

This identifies the maximum number of repetitions of the element that are permitted in a message instance. This attribute should

only be specified if the maximum number of repetitions is greater than 1 and differs from the minimum attribute (i.e. the maximum

number of repetitions is greater than the minimum number of repetitions). The special value '*' may be used to represent 'unlimited' repetitions.

</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

</xs:attribute>

<xs:simpleType name="PathType">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation>

Pattern: (position[instance])(.position[instance])*

where:

- position : the position of an element within its parent. 1

&lt;= position &lt;= nb of children in the parent

- instance : the

repetition number. 1 &lt;= instance &lt;= maximum nuber of

repetitions

</xs:documentation>

</xs:annotation>

<xs:restriction base="xs:string">

<xs:pattern value="[1-9][0-9]*\[(([1-9][0-9]*)|\*)\](\.[1-9][0-9]*\[(([1-9][0-9]*)|\*)\])*|\."/>

</xs:restriction>

</xs:simpleType>

<xs:simpleType name="CommaSeparatedStringType">

<xs:annotation>

<xs:documentation> A comma separated values where each value is an

alphanumeric</xs:documentation>
